If you’ve been on the fence about whether or not you or your child should learn how to play a musical instrument, we’re here to let you know why you should ✨do the thing✨

1. Learning to play an instrument can stimulate the brain and can lead to an increased capacity for memory. 🧠

2. Playing an instrument can improve hand-eye coordination. Think about it! You have to read music notes and then convert that information into motor patterns, in rhythm. You might even try playing with other people, so you need to be able to listen and respond to their instruments as well! 👁🤚👂 

3. When you expose yourself to increasingly difficult pieces of music, you can count on reading & comprehension skills to be boosted! 📚 

4. As you learn more difficult music, you might find that learning an instrument is CHALLENGING. That’s okay! This means it’s a great tool to teach self-discipline. Hard parts need to be practiced again and again, it can take a lot of discipline to do the boring repetitive work—but it is essential in learning ANY new skill. 🧘

5. Music can be a great form of self-expression. As you become more familiar with your instrument, you will find that you have more control over what you play and HOW you choose to play it! Bonus: when the self is expressed, stress levels go down ⬇️
.
.
Check out our website (link in bio) for affordable instruments, exercise books, and even online lessons— We can’t wait to see you on YOUR journey in learning how to play music! 
.
.
.
